      "text": "Interior Light Structure Description - Components"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Map Light/Cargo Area Light"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "It is standard equipment in the center of the roof and at the rear end of the roof. The entry light system is interlocked with door opening/closing and controlled to turn the light on/off. The light can be turned on and off with the ON/OFF switch on the light itself."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Ambient Light"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Tail lights activated by MICU outputs are controlled by a relay to turn on/off the lights."
    }
  ],
